        "description": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes must yield a Grid Convergence Index below 2% for peak volume-averaged shear stress at each of the five COU operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "Mesh refinement study using three levels (3.2M, 9.6M, 28.8M cells) yields a GCI of 4.2% on peak shear stress at the worst-case 6 L/min, 3500 RPM operating point. This exceeds the 2% acceptance threshold. The medium mesh (9.6M cells) was used for all production runs due to computational resource constraints, but convergence to the required threshold was not demonstrated. achievedLevel is 1 (GCI documented but threshold not met)."
    },
    {
