        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Experimental test conditions match COU operating envelope within stated tolerances",
        "description": "Flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, and hematocrit in validation experiments must match COU boundary conditions within ±5% for each parameter."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data (Hariharan et al. 2011) collected at 2, 4, 6 L/min and 2500, 3500 RPM. All five COU operating points fall within the experimental test matrix. Fluid properties (bovine blood, Hct 35%) match COU specification within 3%. Temperature controlled at 37°C ± 0.5°C."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/oc-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/oc-001",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Predicted RH index within 15% of experimental RH at all five operating points",
        "description": "The relative hemolysis index predicted by the CFD power-law model must agree with experimental measurements within 15% at each of the five COU operating points, with uncertainty bounds overlapping."
      },
      "rationale": "Predicted RH index deviates from experimental measurements by 22% at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM worst-case point and 18% at the 4 L/min, 3500 RPM point. These exceed the 15% acceptance threshold. The overprediction is attributed to insufficient mesh resolution at the impeller blade trailing edge (consistent with the GCI shortfall in Discretization error). Uncertainty bounds do not overlap at these two operating points. achievedLevel is 1 (comparison performed and documented but threshold not met at critical operating conditions)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/rqi-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
