        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI directly maps to COU decision metric",
        "description": "The primary quantity of interest (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly traceable to the regulatory decision criterion (RH < 1 vs predicate device)."
      },
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the direct regulatory comparator per FDA guidance. The power-law hemolysis model integrates shear stress and exposure time along Lagrangian particle trajectories, yielding RH as the scalar output. This QoI is the exact metric used in the submission decision criterion."
    },
    {
