        "name": "Validation activities cover COU geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry (FDA generic centrifugal pump), the same flow regime (turbulent, Re > 10000), and blood analog or bovine blood at physiological hematocrit."
      },
      "rationale": "All validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry (identical CAD to the simulation geometry). Flow conditions span the turbulent regime (Re 12000–45000) encompassing all COU operating points. Bovine blood at Hct 35% used in experiments matches the COU fluid specification."
    },
    {
