      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. Nominal input values (geometry dimensions, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are sourced from calibrated measurements with documented uncertainty. Sensitivity of RH to ±5% variation in flow rate and ±2% in rotational speed was evaluated informally and found to produce less than 8% variation in predicted RH."
    },
    {
